about_hlapi_handle.title: What is IxNetwork HLAPI handle?
about_hlapi_handle.description:
A handle is an alphanumeric string, which is an ordered sequence of IxNetwork low level objects separated by a front slash character. It is returned by the HL API commands either in keyed list or in dictionary format. You need to know the proper key to retrieve the corresponding handle and use it in the subsequent HL commands. Handle is a mandatory argument for almost all the HL API commands, like creating new protocols or modifying new protocol stacks etc.
The tables below show how the handles and corresponding keys look like.

code_examples.example: # Creating BGP Stack on top of IPv4 Stack on Port 1 puts "Creating BGP Stack on top of IPv4 Stack in Topology 1" # IPv4 handle will be obtained from interface_config command puts "ipv4 handle = $ipv4_1_handle" set bgp_ipv4_peer_1_status [::ixiangpf::emulation_bgp_config -mode enable -active 1 -handle $ipv4_1_handle -remote_ip_addr 20.20.20.1 ] if {[keylget bgp_ipv4_peer_1_status status] != $::SUCCESS} { puts "FAIL - $test_name - [keylget bgp_ipv4_peer_1_status log]" return 0 } set bgpIpv4Peer_1_handle [keylget bgp_ipv4_peer_1_status bgp_handle] puts "bgpv4 handle = $bgpIpv4Peer_1_handle"
